==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pathogene
<hw>Path"o*gene</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Pathogenic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Any microorganism which causes disease; a pathogenic organism; an
infectious microorganism; a bacterium, virus, or other agent which can
cause disease by infection; -- opposed to <contr>zymogene</contr>. The
spelling <ex>pathogene</ex> is now archaic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pathogenesis</ent>⟦br⟧
